1
00:00:04,521 --> 00:00:07,419
Those who tell us about Kṛṣṇa,

2
00:00:07,435 --> 00:00:10,387
they’re really giving you something.

3
00:00:10,388 --> 00:00:13,583
Now we can understand something
about that.

4
00:00:13,583 --> 00:00:16,665
[Life-saving Talks]

5
00:00:17,172 --> 00:00:20,583
Who brings you the news
about Kṛṣṇa,

6
00:00:20,583 --> 00:00:26,080
there’s no more better messenger
in the world,

7
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:28,755
a greater philanthropist,

8
00:00:28,755 --> 00:00:31,999
there’s nothing better you can do
for somebody

9
00:00:31,999 --> 00:00:35,431
other than introduce them to Kṛṣṇa.

10
00:00:35,431 --> 00:00:37,802
Agreed?

11
00:00:37,802 --> 00:00:40,319
Show of hands.

12
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:45,597
We’re having these programs
at this devotee …

13
00:00:45,597 --> 00:00:49,035
we’re staying in his sister’s room
or something,

14
00:00:49,035 --> 00:00:52,179
and she’s kind of like
going on with everything.

15
00:00:52,179 --> 00:00:53,930
But she sees night after night

16
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:55,801
we’re talking about Kṛṣṇa,
Mahāprabhu, this, that,

17
00:00:55,801 --> 00:00:58,119
and she was saying, like,

18
00:00:58,119 --> 00:01:01,142
“Why don’t you …
If you really want to help people

19
00:01:01,142 --> 00:01:05,582
why don’t you go outside
and distribute some food or something?

20
00:01:05,583 --> 00:01:09,587
Every night you sit here
talking about Kṛṣṇa.”

21
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,457
So I could understand,
she didn’t understand

22
00:01:14,457 --> 00:01:18,056
the value of Hari-kathā,

23
00:01:18,056 --> 00:01:21,174
that it’s tava kathāmṛtaḿ
tapta-jīvanaḿ—
[SB: 10.31.9]

24
00:01:21,174 --> 00:01:24,885
life-giving, life-saving, nectar.

25
00:01:25,209 --> 00:01:28,014
Just to eat some more food

26
00:01:28,014 --> 00:01:30,416
and go on with the death march

27
00:01:30,416 --> 00:01:32,849
in the land of mortality

28
00:01:32,849 --> 00:01:36,078
is not a glorious activity.

